{{Top|leg}}
'''Cynabar''' was a mysterious [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] who operated [[Cynabar's InfoNet/Legends|Cynabar's InfoNet]] during the time of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="GNN3">{{JournalCite|3|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>

Cynabar also regularly put out [[Cynabar's Droid Datalog]], a [[Scandoc/Legends|scandoc]] regarding [[Droid/Legends|droids]] and their usefulness to smugglers, which contained data collated from various [[NewsNet|newsnets]] and data archives.<ref name="GNN3" />

[[TriNebulon News/Legends|TriNebulon News]] journalist [[Andor Javin]] once claimed that Cynabar was none other than the notorious [[Brentaalan]] smuggler [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]]. However, since Javin's journalistic methodology was far from meticulous, the identification of Cynabar as Okeefe is tenuous at best.<ref name="GNN3" />

Cynabar refused to say how many [[Shadowport/Legends|shadowports]] they had been to, but did reveal that the number was closer to fifty than it was to forty.<ref name="GNN3" />

Cynabar was friends with [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].<ref name="Heroes & Rogues">''[[Heroes & Rogues]]'', p18</ref> Conversely, [[Triege|Lord Triege's]] [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]] fleet was dedicated to hunting down Cynabar for the Empire.<ref name="GNN3" />

